This is a very particular problem that happens if you do somthing very specific to cause this problem.
If you are having trouble with blender closing out after you alt+tab or minimized it.
This might be the solution for you so you can get back to work on those Vrchat models and worlds again.

If you have purchased a XP Tablet or a Wacom Tablet and has disabled pentablet on startup,
then it has to relate to this.

Me and my friend had the same problem but we fixed it for us.
What we found out was that we both had xp pen tablet and a wacom tablet and we both disabled on start up "'''pentablet sevices'''".

'''Step 1''' : Open your task manager.

'''Step 2''' : Click on the startup tab.

'''Step 3''' : Right click and Enable pentablet services. (close out of it)

'''Step 4''' : Next right click windows start button, click search.

'''Step 5''' : Search for "pentablet" application, Run it.

(You will get a prompt that says "can't detect tablet, please plug it into then open the driver again" you do not have to plug in your tablet.)

'''Step 6''' : Just Click OK


And wahlah blender is able to tab out and tab back in again. Hope this helps you guys out ^^
